Byrone Athman PHOTO: suppliedUKZN cricket team members are all smiles at the weekend. Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories BOTH University of KwaZulu-Natal cricket teams were victorious last weekend after winning their respective T20 leagues and being crowned at the Pietermaritzburg Oval. The teams that play in the Premier Division and the First Division put in brilliant effort at the weekend as the transformed club looks to continue pushing forward its youngsters at the forefront of the team. Yashveer Singh, coaching manager at the KwaZulu-Natal Cricket Union, congratulated all who were involved in the cricket club’s success this season. “Thanks to all the leaders in both teams for leading the youngsters and ensuring that they grow from strength to strength in this great game. “It was a brilliant effort put forward by both teams and we will look to continue upon this success going forward,” said Singh. Singh also congratulated the teams in the third and fourth divisions on their wins and being runners up in the other divisions, stating that it was an excellent weekend for the growth of cricket.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.